.TH "drm_helper_force_disable_all" 9 "drm_helper_force_disable_all" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_helper_force_disable_all \- Forcibly turn off all enabled CRTCs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_helper_force_disable_all
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device whose CRTCs to turn off
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Drivers may want to call this on unload to ensure that all displays are
unlit and the GPU is in a consistent, low power state. Takes modeset locks.
.SH "NOTE"
This should only be used by non-atomic legacy drivers. For an atomic
version look at \fBdrm_atomic_helper_shutdown\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, error code on failure.
